  "text": "The Kubernetes admission webhook processing chain is implemented across the k8s.io/apiserver and k8s.io/api repositories, with the following components:\n\n## Plugin Entry Points\nThe processing chain starts with two admission plugins:\n1. **MutatingAdmissionWebhook** (pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/plugin.go:Plugin) - Implements admission.MutationInterface and routes requests through its Admit() method\n2. **ValidatingAdmissionWebhook** (pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/validating/plugin.go:Plugin) - Implements admission.ValidationInterface and routes requests through its Validate() method\n\n## Generic Webhook Infrastructure\nThe generic.Webhook (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/generic/webhook.go) provides the common infrastructure for both webhook types:\n- **Webhook struct**: Manages webhook configuration, client management, namespace/object matchers, and dispatchers\n- **ShouldCallHook()**: Evaluates webhook predicates including namespace selectors, object selectors, rules matching, match policy (Equivalent), and CEL-based match conditions\n- **Dispatch()**: Routes the request to the appropriate dispatcher (mutating or validating)\n\nThe generic.Webhook delegates to specialized Dispatcher implementations through the Dispatcher interface (generic/interfaces.go).\n\n## Dispatcher Implementations\n\n### Mutating Webhook Dispatcher\nThe mutatingDispatcher (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/dispatcher.go) implements sophisticated reinvocation logic:\n- **Sequential processing**: Iterates through hooks in order\n- **Reinvocation tracking**: Uses webhookReinvokeContext to track which webhooks should be reinvoked if mutations occur\n- **Change detection**: Compares object state before and after each webhook invocation\n- **Reinvocation policy**: Respects the ReinvocationPolicy field (IfNeededReinvocationPolicy) to determine which webhooks are eligible for reinvocation\n- **Patch application**: Applies JSON patches from mutating webhooks and handles object serialization/deserialization\n\nThe reinvocationcontext.go file defines webhookReinvokeContext which tracks:\n- lastWebhookOutput: Object state from the last webhook invocation\n- previouslyInvokedReinvocableWebhooks: Webhooks that can be reinvoked if mutations occur\n- reinvokeWebhooks: Webhooks that should be reinvoked in the current round\n\n### Validating Webhook Dispatcher\nThe validatingDispatcher (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/validating/dispatcher.go) implements parallel webhook execution:\n- **Parallel dispatch**: Uses goroutines with sync.WaitGroup to call multiple validating webhooks concurrently\n- **Error handling**: Collects errors from all goroutines and returns the first error\n- **Panic recovery**: Implements proper panic recovery and crash handling for each goroutine\n- **Failure policy support**: Respects Ignore failure policy to continue on webhook call failures\n- **Versioned attribute caching**: Caches VersionedAttributes by GroupVersionKind to reuse across parallel calls\n\n## WebhookAccessor Abstraction Layer\nThe WebhookAccessor interface (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/accessors.go) provides a unified abstraction over both mutating and validating webhooks:\n- **Getter methods**: Provides access to webhook configuration fields (Name, ClientConfig, Rules, FailurePolicy, MatchPolicy, etc.)\n- **Selector methods**: Exposes namespace and object label selectors\n- **Client management**: GetRESTClient() lazily initializes webhook clients using sync.Once\n- **Match condition compilation**: Compiles CEL-based match conditions through GetCompiledMatcher()\n- **Type differentiation**: GetMutatingWebhook() and GetValidatingWebhook() allow callers to determine webhook type\n\nTwo implementations are provided:\n1. mutatingWebhookAccessor: Wraps v1.MutatingWebhook\n2. validatingWebhookAccessor: Wraps v1.ValidatingWebhook\n\n## Configuration Management\nThe configuration managers in pkg/admission/configuration provide dynamic webhook discovery:\n\n1. **mutatingWebhookConfigurationManager** (mutating_webhook_manager.go):\n   - Watches MutatingWebhookConfiguration resources via SharedInformerFactory\n   - Maintains a cache of loaded configurations\n   - Provides merged webhook accessors via Webhooks()\n   - Uses lazy evaluation with synctrack.Lazy for efficient updates\n\n2. **validatingWebhookConfigurationManager** (validating_webhook_manager.go):\n   - Similar structure for ValidatingWebhookConfiguration resources\n   - Also implements the generic.Source interface\n\n## API Type Definitions\nThe admissionregistration/v1 API types (api/admissionregistration/v1/types.go) define:\n\n1. **MutatingWebhookConfiguration**: Cluster-scoped resource containing a list of MutatingWebhook entries\n2. **ValidatingWebhookConfiguration**: Cluster-scoped resource containing a list of ValidatingWebhook entries\n3. **MutatingWebhook**: Individual webhook configuration with:\n   - ClientConfig: Connection details\n   - Rules: Resource matching rules\n   - NamespaceSelector/ObjectSelector: Label selectors for filtering\n   - MatchConditions: CEL expressions for fine-grained matching\n   - ReinvocationPolicy: Controls reinvocation eligibility (IfNeededReinvocationPolicy)\n   - SideEffects: Declares side effects for dry-run validation\n   - TimeoutSeconds: Individual webhook timeout\n   - FailurePolicy: How to handle webhook errors (Ignore or Fail)\n4. **ValidatingWebhook**: Similar structure to MutatingWebhook but without ReinvocationPolicy\n\n## Processing Chain Flow\nFor a request:\n1. Plugin.Admit() or Plugin.Validate() is called\n2. Webhook.Dispatch() routes to the appropriate dispatcher\n3. Dispatcher iterates through WebhookAccessor entries from configuration managers\n4. For each webhook, ShouldCallHook() evaluates predicates and match conditions\n5. If webhook applies:\n   - Mutating: Serializes request, calls webhook, applies patches, tracks changes for reinvocation\n   - Validating: Calls webhook in parallel, collects results from all goroutines\n6. Returns accumulated errors or allows request to proceed\n\nThe design enables dynamic webhook discovery (via informers), lazy resource conversion (via VersionedAttributeAccessor), and efficient concurrent validation while maintaining serial mutation with intelligent reinvocation support."
